
Overview of noun microwave

The noun microwave has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (2) microwave -- (a short electromagnetic wave (longer than infrared but shorter than radio waves); used for radar and microwave ovens and for transmitting telephone, facsimile, video and data)
2. microwave, microwave oven -- (kitchen appliance that cooks food by passing an electromagnetic wave through it; heat results from the absorption of energy by the water molecules in the food)

Overview of verb microwave

The verb microwave has 1 sense (no senses from tagged texts)
                                     
1. microwave, micro-cook, zap, nuke -- (cook or heat in a microwave oven; "You can microwave the leftovers")
